    <ns0:content type="html">&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;URL:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/OpenPOWERFoundation/a2o"&gt;https://github.com/OpenPOWERFoundation/a2o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language:&lt;/strong&gt; verilog&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The A2O core was a follow-on to A2I, written in Verilog, and supported a lower thread count than A2I, but higher performance per thread, using out-of-order execution (register renaming, reservation stations, completion buffer) and a store queue. It is now being updated for compliancy and integration into open projects.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</ns0:content>
